      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "A robust, modern approach to border security must prioritize national sovereignty and the rule of law above all else. Increased funding and stricter enforcement are not punitive measures; they are essential infrastructure investments to manage national security risks, including drug trafficking and transnational crime. Furthermore, a secure border allows for orderly legal immigration, which benefits the economy, rather than allowing uncontrolled entry that strains public resources.",
